1. My C1 and C2 vertebrates are significantly rotated. For that, I‚Äôve been seeing a chiro 2-3x a week for around 6 weeks, with no relief. And that‚Äôs because:

2. My first rib is significantly elevated. Between the both of these, and the fact this has been going on for so long, all of the muscles in my neck and shoulder are very, VERY tight. They don‚Äôt want to relax and let go, and it‚Äôs making it very hard to get everything back into its‚Äôs proper place. 

3. Additionally, my shoulder and scapular muscles are pretty weak. üò© They‚Äôre not doing the work they should and my neck is compensating. 

All of this has been a huge wake up call into the importance proper alignment. So much of my yoga is done through my shoulders...

Here‚Äôs hoping between PT and chiro, I can get some relief soon. üôèüèª

